<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Merkvah of Tallon Zek</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-19 14:59:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I've played to lvl 29 as a paladin, and I think I know enough to say that damage, while nice, is not the tank's forte.  The best thing a tank can do is to taunt and take hits.  After a fight once, we were all sitting around comparing damage, and I was pretty proud of myself.  My new GZ had hit for 46 pts.  Unfortunately, I was the highest lvl in the group and everyone else had hit for 126 or 145 pts with their spells.  I was also the only one who had lost any life.  If I had been more concerned with taking the mob down than i was with protecting my finger wavers, it's very likely that I would have been the only one who survived...<BR>
<BR>
so why post this here?<BR>
I have a buddy who plays on Povar.  He had full crafted at 26.  Most of his crafted by 24.  I was excited, because I expected to have my Ro armor by then, right?  nope.  Most sites recommend not even starting on Ro until lvl 33, and most paladins I know of dont' have it till lvl 40 or 45.  Read a recient post somewhere about a paladin completeing her Ro armor as early as 44, and everyone was congratulating her.  so we paladins get a nice sword?  (FYI, there is only ONE person, on ANY server who has one - Musk, of the Tunare server, so it's NOT easy)  Big deal.  I will probably never wield one.  BTW, I'm still in Bronze armor.  it's the best I can get at 29.<BR>
<BR>
Merkvah Holyblade<BR>
29th Circle Paladin of Tunare<BR>
Knight of the Koada Vie<BR>
