<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>First off....the COF haste is more like 25 not 40, no item has 40 haste.  The highest haste is on the Sunderfury, which is 35%.  And yes, that makes the Sunderfury the more damaging weapon.  With the FA and COF the ratio ends up more like...20 ratio flat.  That plus the proc and stats still make this one fucking kick ass weapon.  The Sunderfury, however, has a 35% haste, and with that gets up to a delay of 23, making have a better ratio than the FA, but no proc. The Jade Inlaid Crecent Axe with COF is also better than the FA, but not the sunderfury...interesting no?  But yes the Rod of Annihilation blows anything away.  Funny joke Verant! You really get a kick out of pissing off a lot of people!  I am a warrior but IMHO I just want a quest sword because it would be fun, not for better stats.  I am already only planning on a Monsoon just for stats and looks (19 ratio with its haste).  I think that both Pals and Wars will agree that a quest sword for wars would be just fun to have, because Wars miss having quests at the higher levels.  And as for SKs....they Deserve the exact same damn sword because they get the shit just as much as pallys.  Warriors would have it for fun but Verant needs to stop screwing over Sks.  Rangers also now have a decent weapon off of kunark, but all in all the quests are just for fun.  Thank you  </font></td></tr></table>
